{% set singleCode %}<video-player>
  <video controls poster="poster.jpg" width="960" height="540">
    <source src="video.mp4" type="video/mp4">
    <track kind="captions" src="en.vtt" srclang="en" label="English" default>
    <p><a href="video.mp4" download>Download video</a></p>
  </video>
</video-player>{% endset %}

{% set playlistCode %}<video-player>
  <video controls poster="ep1.jpg" width="960" height="540">
    <source src="episodes/01.mp4" type="video/mp4">
    <track kind="captions" src="captions/01-en.vtt" srclang="en" label="English" default>
  </video>
  <details>
    <summary>Episodes</summary>
    <ol class="track-list">
      <li data-video-active>
        <a href="episodes/01.mp4" data-poster="ep1.jpg" data-captions="captions/01-en.vtt">01. Introduction</a>
        <span class="track-meta"><time datetime="PT12M30S">12:30</time></span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="episodes/02.mp4" data-poster="ep2.jpg">02. Getting Started</a>
        <span class="track-meta"><time datetime="PT18M45S">18:45</time></span>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </details>
</video-player>{% endset %}

{% set shuffleCode %}<video-player data-shuffle data-loop>
  <video controls poster="ep1.jpg" width="960" height="540">
    <source src="episodes/01.mp4" type="video/mp4">
  </video>
  <details open>
    <summary>Shuffle Playlist</summary>
    <ol class="track-list">
      <li data-video-active><a href="episodes/01.mp4">Episode 1</a></li>
      <li><a href="episodes/02.mp4">Episode 2</a></li>
      <li><a href="episodes/03.mp4">Episode 3</a></li>
    </ol>
  </details>
</video-player>{% endset %}

{% set customCode %}video-player {
  --video-player-accent: oklch(60% 0.2 30);
  --video-player-radius: var(--radius-l);
  --video-player-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
  --video-player-controls-bg: oklch(0% 0 0 / 0.85);
  --video-player-timeline-height: 6px;
}{% endset %}

{% set eventCode %}const player = document.querySelector('video-player');

player.addEventListener('vb:video:play', (e) => {
  console.log('Playing:', e.detail.src);
});

player.addEventListener('vb:video:track-change', (e) => {
  console.log('Now playing:', e.detail.title);
});

player.addEventListener('vb:video:fullscreen', (e) => {
  console.log('Fullscreen:', e.detail.active);
});

player.addEventListener('vb:video:speed', (e) => {
  console.log('Speed:', e.detail.rate);
});{% endset %}

{% set fallbackCode %}<!-- Without JS: native <video> controls render and work.
     Poster, captions, and track list links all function. -->
<video-player>
  <video controls poster="poster.jpg" width="960" height="540">
    <source src="video.mp4" type="video/mp4">
    <track kind="captions" src="en.vtt" srclang="en" label="English" default>
    <p><a href="video.mp4" download>Download video</a></p>
  </video>
</video-player>{% endset %}

<section>
  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>A platform-native video player that wraps <code>&lt;video&gt;</code> in light DOM and renders custom overlay controls in shadow DOM. Controls fade in on interaction and auto-hide during playback. The native player is always the fallback — if JS is unavailable, <code>&lt;video controls&gt;</code> works normally with poster, captions, and fullscreen.</p>

  <browser-window
    src="/docs/examples/demos/video-player-basic.html"
    url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/video-player"
    title="Video Player"
    shadow>
  </browser-window>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Single Video</h2>
  <p>Wrap a native <code>&lt;video&gt;</code> with optional <code>&lt;track&gt;</code> elements for captions.</p>
  <browser-window
    src="/docs/snippets/demos/video-player-single.html"
    url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/video-player/single"
    title="Single Video"
    shadow>
  </browser-window>
  <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Wrapping a single video element">{{ singleCode | escape }}</code-block>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Sizing</h2>
  <p>Always include <code>width</code> and <code>height</code> attributes on the <code>&lt;video&gt;</code> element. These give the browser intrinsic dimensions <strong>before metadata loads</strong>, preventing layout shift — the same best practice as <code>&lt;img&gt;</code>.</p>
  <p>For remote or large video files, the browser may not have loaded metadata (and therefore the video's native dimensions) by the time the page renders. Without dimension hints, the player collapses to zero height until the remote file responds.</p>
  <p>The component also applies <code>aspect-ratio: 16/9</code> as a CSS fallback. Once the video's actual aspect ratio is known from metadata or the poster image, it overrides the CSS default automatically. If your video is not 16:9, the <code>width</code>/<code>height</code> attributes ensure the correct ratio is used from the start.</p>
  <p>A <code>poster</code> image is strongly recommended — it provides visual content before playback and helps the browser establish dimensions early.</p>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Playlist Mode</h2>
  <p>Include a <code>&lt;details&gt;</code> with <code>&lt;ol class="track-list"&gt;</code> inside the component. Clicking a track updates the video source and plays it. Use <code>data-poster</code> and <code>data-captions</code> on track links for per-video switching.</p>
  <browser-window
    src="/docs/snippets/demos/video-player-playlist.html"
    url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/video-player/playlist"
    title="Video Playlist"
    shadow>
  </browser-window>
  <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Video player with playlist">{{ playlistCode | escape }}</code-block>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Shuffle and Loop</h2>
  <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Shuffle playlist with loop">{{ shuffleCode | escape }}</code-block>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Controls Behavior</h2>
  <p>Unlike <code>&lt;audio-player&gt;</code> which shows a permanent control bar, video controls are an <strong>overlay</strong> that fades in and out:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Visible for 3 seconds after any interaction (mousemove, focus, keypress)</li>
    <li>Always visible when paused, before first play, or after ended</li>
    <li>Touch devices: tap toggles visibility</li>
    <li>Cursor hides when controls are hidden during playback</li>
    <li><code>prefers-reduced-motion</code>: controls stay permanently visible</li>
  </ul>
  <p>A gradient scrim at the bottom ensures controls are readable over any video content.</p>
</section>

